The paper focuses on adaptive bitrate video streaming over wireless networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a crowdsourced framework for cooperative video streaming, which involves multiple users and can be considered a form of multimedia systems (cs.MM) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also formulates the associated optimization problem as a linear programming, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT).
